{"id":27199885071,"name":"Run api tests","node_id":"WFR_kwLOA_1uaM8AAAAGVT1PDw","head_branch":"security/2.38","head_sha":"6d7b08e2b2b3616792fdff9bd4049d0f7ee05230","path":".github/workflows/run-api-tests.yml","run_number":50405,"run_attempt":1,"event":"pull_request","display_title":"security backport:#148 → 2.38","status":"completed","conclusion":"success","workflow_id":5591308,"check_suite_id":73081528378,"check_suite_node_id":"CS_kwDOA_1uaM8AAAARA_-gOg","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/27199885071","html_url":"https://github.com/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/27199885071","created_at":"2026-06-09T10:25:27Z","updated_at":"2026-06-09T10:37:46Z","run_started_at":"2026-06-09T10:25:27Z","jobs_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/27199885071/jobs","logs_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/27199885071/logs","check_suite_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/check-suites/73081528378","artifacts_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/27199885071/artifacts","cancel_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/27199885071/cancel","rerun_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/27199885071/rerun","head_commit":{"message":"fix: quote SQL view filter column name to block identifier-slot injection\n\nThe filter column name was concatenated raw into the generated WHERE\nclause in DefaultSqlViewService.getFilterQuery, mirroring the same\nshape that getCriteriaSqlClause already handles correctly via\nstatementBuilder.columnQuote(). Two independent reports demonstrate\nthe missed sink is exploitable for arbitrary SQL execution by any\nauthenticated user with read access to a SQL View:\n\n- GHSA-pwmg-mvjw-4m23 — error-based exfil via CAST((subquery) AS int)\n- internal report — UNION SELECT smuggled through the column-name slot\n\nWrapping the column name with statementBuilder.columnQuote() turns the\nwhole user-supplied string into a single Postgres identifier, which\nPostgres rejects at parse time when it doesn't exist — preventing the\ninner SQL from being evaluated. This is exactly the defense already\nin place for the parallel sink in getCriteriaSqlClause.\n\nNote: the master/2.40-2.42 backports use SqlUtils.quote() and ship\ncompanion regression tests in SqlViewControllerIntegrationTest. On\n2.38 the matching defense API is statementBuilder.columnQuote() and\nthe regression test class does not exist, so only the fix is applied.\n\nAI Assisted\n\nRefs GHSA-pwmg-mvjw-4m23, DHIS2-21425","author":{"name":"Morten Svanaes","email":"msvanaes@dhis2.org"},"id":"6d7b08e2b2b3616792fdff9bd4049d0f7ee05230","tree_id":"d1a1cb48512ba515fb75464e8e43ca7ab67c68c4","timestamp":"2026-06-09T10:25:13Z","committer":{"name":"Morten Svanaes","email":"msvanaes@dhis2.org"}},"workflow_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/workflows/5591308","repository":{"id":66940520,"node_id":"MDEwOlJlcG9zaXRvcnk2Njk0MDUyMA==","owner":{"login":"dhis2","id":1089987,"node_id":"MDEyOk9yZ2FuaXphdGlvbjEwODk5ODc=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1089987?v=4","html_url":"https://github.com/dhis2","gravatar_id":"","type":"Organization","site_admin":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/events{/privacy}","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/following{/other_user}","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/followers","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/gists{/gist_id}","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/orgs","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/received_events","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/repos","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/subscriptions"},"name":"dhis2-core","full_name":"dhis2/dhis2-core","description":"DHIS 2 Core. Writt